<Author>Burracooka
<Content>Wonderful Stay Have just returned from the 4S Singapore  really wanted to pass on my good experience. The hotel was wonderful in so many ways. The staff couldnt do enough for you, always remembered your name, were efficient and helpful and made an enormous effort to make sure we were comfortable at all times.A special mention should be made of the Spa, its Director and the 1 particular Massage Therapist who took care of my elderly mother. She was very reluctant and was very sensitive to her body and her recent hip replacement. The Therapist was superb to her! Very gently, helpful to the point of escorting her to and from the change room and taking her down in the Service Lift so she didnt have to walk down all the steps back to the Spa Reception. We so appreciated these little kind touches!In terms of hardware, our suite was lovely - well equipped, clean and spacious. It must be said that they could probably do with an update. As mentioned here before, they are starting to look a little dowdy! Also, the in-house TV could do with a SERIOUS revamp!Our only drama with the hotel was the checking out process and the bill. We were leaving very early in the morning so requested the account the night before so that we could settle up the majority of the bill and in the morning settle the remainders - room service dinner and 1 international telephone call to home in the morning. We went through this with the girl working out our account and she seemed to understand. Finally the bill was sent up to us with several items billed to us instead of taken off as they were items included in our package ie: 2 x massages  1 x dimsum lunch. We had to go through quite an ordeal to assure them that they were in fact inclusive items. Finally, they agreed  revised the account. Next morning we go downstairs to see the SAME GIRL - pay the last items (rs dinner  a $3 phone call) and she tries to bill us for the room tariff again for the previous night - despite having already charged us  being the one who prepped the bill the night before!Perhaps Im being petty - but I thought this was almost unforgiveable at a hotel of this standing. Also, it was the last dealing we had with the hotel - not a great way to leave our stay!Such a shame a silly thing like this should occur.Dont let it put you off though - just be very careful  check your bill, perhaps even bring your confirmation email/letter (which we didnt) just in case you need to wave in someones face!All in all - everything else and everyone else outweighed this little inconvenience.Enjoy! 
